THIS DOCUMENT CONTAINS A LIST OF FUNCTIONS BUILT INTO XPINS
NOTE: Any function that Takes a FLOAT can be passed an INT instead.

BOOLEAN LOGIC

X_AND(BOOL $A,BOOL $B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Evaultes the statement A AND B
	Parameters: The booleans to be tested for AND
	Return: BOOL, returns true if and only if both A and B are true.

X_OR(BOOL $A,BOOL $B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Evaultes the statement A OR B
	Parameters: The booleans to be tested for OR
	Return: BOOL, returns true if either A or B is true.

X_NOT(BOOL $A)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Evaultes the statement NOT A
	Parameters: The booleans to be inverted
	Return: BOOL, returns true if and only if A is false
					



NUMBER COMPARISON

X_LESS(FLOAT $A,FLOAT $B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Evaultes the expression A<B
	Parameters: The FLOATs to be compared
	Return: BOOL, returns true if A is less than B
	
X_MORE(FLOAT $A,FLOAT $B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Evaultes the expression A>B
	Parameters: The FLOATs to be compared
	Return: BOOL, returns true if A is greater than B

	
X_EQUAL(FLOAT $A,FLOAT $B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Evaultes the expression A==B
	Parameters: The FLOATs to be compared
	Return: BOOL, returns true if A is equal to B
						



ARITHMETIC

X_ADD(FLOAT $A, FLOAT $B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Evaultes the expression A+B
	Parameters: The FLOATs to be added
	Return: FLOAT, returns the sum of A and B
	
X_SUB(FLOAT $A, FLOAT $B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Evaultes the expression A-B
	Parameters: The FLOATs to be subtracted
	Return: FLOAT, returns the difference of A and B

X_MULT(FLOAT $A, FLOAT $B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Evaultes the expression A*B
	Parameters: The FLOATs to be multiplied
	Return: FLOAT, returns the product of A and B

X_DIV(FLOAT $A, FLOAT $B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Evaultes the expression A/B
	Parameters: The FLOATs to be divided
	Return: FLOAT, returns the quotient of A and B
					
X_MOD(INT $A, INT $B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.4.0
	Description: Evaultes the expression A%B
	Parameters: The INTs to be modulated
	Return: INT, returns the modulus of A and B



TRIGONOMETRY

X_TSIN(FLOAT $A)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Takes the sine of a given angle
	Parameters: The FLOAT representing the angle
	Return: FLOAT, returns the sine of the angle

X_TCOS(FLOAT $A)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Takes the cosine of a given angle
	Parameters: The FLOAT representing the angle
	Return: FLOAT, returns the cosine of the angle
	
X_TTAN(FLOAT $A)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Takes the tangent of a given angle
	Parameters: The FLOAT representing the angle
	Return: FLOAT, returns the tangent of the angle

X_TATAN(FLOAT $A, FLOAT $B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Gets the base angle given the two legs of a right triangle
	Parameters: The FLOATs representing Y and X, repsectiely
	Return: FLOAT, returns the angle

X_VADDPOLAR(FLOAT $A, FLOAT $B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Adds two numbers such that the sum is in the range of [0,2PI)
	Parameters: The FLOATs to be added
	Return: FLOAT, returns the modified sum of A and B
					



OTHER SCALAR MATH OPERATIONS

X_POW(FLOAT $A, FLOAT $B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Evaluates A^B
	Parameters: FLOATs representing the base and exponent, respectively
	Return: FLOAT, returns the result of the power exrpession

X_VDIST(FLOAT $A, FLOAT $B, FLOAT $C)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Finds distance between two points given the components
	Parameters: The X, Y, and Z deltas
	Return: FLOAT, returns sqrt(x^2+y^2+z^2);

X_RAND(INT $A, INT$B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Generates a random number
	Parameters: A is the lower bound and B is the upper bound
	Return: INT, returns a random number between A and B
					



VECTOR CREATION

X_VREC(FLOAT $A, FLOAT $B, FLOAT $C)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Creates a vector using rectangular components
	Parameters: FLOATs representing the X, Y, and Z components, respectively
	Return: VEC, returns a new vector with the given components
	
X_VPOL(FLOAT $A, FLOAT $B, FLOAT $C)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Creates a vector using polar components
	Parameters: FLOATs representing the R, THETA, and Z components, respectively
	Return: VEC, returns a new vector with the given components
	
X_VSPHERE(FLOAT $A, FLOAT $B, FLOAT $C)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Creates a vector using polar components
	Parameters: FLOATs representing the RHO, THETA, and PHI components, respectively
	Return: VEC, returns a new vector with the given components


READING VECTORS

X_VX(VEC $A)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Gets the X component for a Vector
	Parameters: The vector for which the X component is desired
	Return: FLOAT, returns the X component of the vector

X_VY(VEC $A)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Gets the Y component for a Vector
	Parameters: The vector for which the Y component is desired
	Return: FLOAT, returns the Y component of the vector

X_VZ(VEC $A)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.8.0
	Description: Gets the Z component for a Vector
	Parameters: The vector for which the Z component is desired
	Return: FLOAT, returns the Z component of the vector

X_VRHO(VEC $A)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Gets the Magnitude (RHO) of a Vector
	Parameters: The vector for which the Magnitude is desired
	Return: FLOAT, returns the Magnitude of the vector
	
X_VR(VEC $A)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.8.0
	Description: Gets the Cylindrical R component of a Vector
	Parameters: The vector for which the Cylindrical R component is desired
	Return: FLOAT, returns the Cylindrical R component of the vector


X_VTHETA(VEC $A)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Gets the THETA component of Vector
	Parameters: The vector for which the THETA component is desired
	Return: FLOAT, returns the THETA component of the vector

X_VPHI(VEC $A)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.8.0
	Description: Gets the PHI component for a Vector
	Parameters: The vector for which the PHI component is desired
	Return: FLOAT, returns the PHI component of the vector


VECTOR OPERATIONS


X_VANG(VEC $A, VEC$B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Finds the angle between two vectors
	Parameters: The vectors for which you want to find the angle between
	Return: FLOAT, returns the Angle between the Vectors

X_VADD(VEC $A, VEC $B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Adds two vectors
	Parameters: The vectors to be added
	Return: VEC, returns the sum of the two vectors
	
X_VSUB(VEC $A, VEC $B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Subtracts two vectors
	Parameters: The vectors to be subtracted
	Return: VEC, returns the difference of the two vectors
	
X_VSCALE(VEC $A, FLOAT $B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.2.0
	Description: Scales a vector
	Parameters: The vector to be scaled, and the FLOAT by which to scale it
	
X_VDOT(VEC $A, VEC $B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.3.0
	Description: Finds the dot product of two vectors
	Parameters: The vectors for which the dot product will be found
	Return: FLOAT, returns A dot B.

X_VCROSS(VEC $A, VEC $B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.8.0
	Description: Finds the cross product of two vectors
	Parameters: The vectors for which the cross product will be found
	Return: VEC, returns A cross B.

X_VPROJ(VEC $A, FLOAT $B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.3.0
	Description: Finds the projection of a vector onto a generic vector in a given direction
	Parameters: The vector from whihc the projection is to be taken, and the direction of the result.
	Return: VEC, returns the projection of A onto a vector in direction.	Return: VEC, returns a vector in the same direction as A with the magnitude multiplied by B
	
	
MATRIX CREATION

X_MMAKE(INT $A, INT $B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.9.0
	Description: Create a Zero Matrix
	Parameters: The number of rows and columns, respecitvely
	Return: MAT, returns a zero matrix of size AxB.
	
X_MID(INT $A)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.9.0
	Description: Create an Identity Matrix of size A
	Parameters: The number of rows and columns.
	Return: MAT, returns a Identity matrix of size AxA.
	
X_MROT(FLOAT $A, VEC $B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.9.0
	Description: Create an Rotation Matrix of A radians around B
	Parameters: A is the angle the Matrix will rotate a vector, and B is the vector that it should be rotated around
	Return: MAT, returns a Rotation matrix A radains around B.
	
	
MATRIX ACCESS

X_MGET(MAT $A, INT $B, INT$C)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.9.0
	Description: Gets a value from a Matrix
	Parameters: A is the matrix, B is the row, and C is the column
	Return: FLOAT, Value from A at B,C
	
X_MSET(MAT $A, FLOAT $B, INT $C, INT $D)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.9.0
	Description: Sets a value in a Matrix
	Parameters: A is the matrix, B is the new value, C is the row, and D is the column
	Return: NONE
	

MATRIX-VECTOR CONVERSTION


X_MMTV(MAT $A)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.9.0
	Description: Converts Matrix into Vector
	Parameters: The Matrix to be converted
	Return: VEC, Vector from Matrix A
	
X_MVTM(VEC $A)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.9.0
	Description: Converts Vector into Matrix
	Parameters: The Vector to be converted
	Return: MAT, Matrix from Vector A
	
	
MATRIX ARITHMETIC

X_MADD(MAT $A, MAT $B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.9.0
	Description: Adds two Matrices
	Parameters: The Matrices to be added
	Return: MAT, Sum of the two Matrices
	
X_MSUB(MAT $A, MAT $B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.9.0
	Description: Subtracts two Matrices
	Parameters: The Matrices to be subtracted
	Return: MAT, Difference of the two Matrices
	
X_MSCALE(MAT $A, FLOAT $B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.9.0
	Description: Multiplies a Matrix by a scalar
	Parameters: The Matrix and the Scalar
	Return: MAT, Product of a Scalar and  a Matrix

X_MMULT(MAT $A, MAT $B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.9.0
	Description: Multiplies two Matrices
	Parameters: The Matrices to be multiplied
	Return: MAT, product of the two Matrices

X_MVMULT(MAT $A, VEC $B)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.9.0
	Description: Multiplies a Matrix and a Vector
	Parameters: The Matrix and Vector to be multiplied
	Return: VEC, product of the Matrix and the Vector
	

ADVANCED MATRIX OPERATIONS

X_MDET(MAT $A)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.9.0
	Description: Finds the determinant of a Matrix
	Parameters: The Matrix for which the determinant is desired
	Return: FLOAT, the Determinant of the Matrix
	
X_MINV(MAT $A)
	Available in XPINS Parser: 0.9.0
	Description: Finds the inverse of a Matrix
	Parameters: The Matrix for which the inverse is desired
	Return: MAT, the inverse of the Matrix
	
X_MTRANS(MAT $A)
	Description: Finds the transposition of a Matrix
	Parameters: The Matrix for which the transposition is desired
	Return: FLOAT, the transposition of the Matrix


	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	

	
